Hi Manik,

Draw some curve.  Now take a ruler, and start moving the ruler towards
the curve until it touches at exactly one point.  The line represented
by the ruler is a tangent to the curve at that point. 

'Tangent' is also the name of a trigonometric function:

  Trigonometry in a Nutshell
  http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/view/53942.html

Does this help?

- Doctor Ian, The Math Forum
